---
import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "France Work Visa Insurance Guide 2025 | Talent Passport & Salarié Requirements";
const description = "Complete guide to France work visa insurance requirements. Covers Talent Passport, Salarié visa, Sécurité Sociale enrollment, and health coverage for working in France.";

const tocItems = [
  { id: "overview", label: "Overview" },
  { id: "quick-decision", label: "Is This Right for You?" },
  { id: "official-requirements", label: "Official Requirements" },
  { id: "insurance-requirements", label: "Insurance Requirements" },
  { id: "recommended-providers", label: "Recommended Providers" },
  { id: "costs", label: "Costs Breakdown" },
  { id: "application-timeline", label: "Application Timeline" },
  { id: "scenarios", label: "Real-World Scenarios" },
  { id: "common-mistakes", label: "Common Mistakes" },
  { id: "healthcare-access", label: "Healthcare Access" },
  { id: "faq", label: "FAQs" },
  { id: "verdict", label: "Final Verdict" }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <PageShell
    title="France Work Visa Insurance Guide"
    subtitle="Your complete guide to working legally in France with proper health coverage"
    heroImage="/images/countries/france-hero-bg.png"
    tocItems={tocItems}
  >
    <!-- Quick Facts Box -->
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-4">Quick Facts: France Work Visa</h3>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div><strong>Visa Types:</strong> Talent Passport, Salarié, EU Blue Card</div>
        <div><strong>Initial Duration:</strong> 1-4 years (renewable)</div>
        <div><strong>Salary Threshold:</strong> 1.5-2x minimum wage (role dependent)</div>
        <div><strong>Processing Time:</strong> 2-4 months</div>
        <div><strong>Health Insurance:</strong> Sécurité Sociale (mandatory enrollment)</div>
        <div><strong>PR Pathway:</strong> Carte de résident after 5 years</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Overview -->
    <section id="overview" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Overview</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        France offers several work visa pathways, with the Talent Passport (Passeport Talent) being the most attractive for skilled professionals. Unlike traditional work permits requiring lengthy labor market tests, the Talent Passport streamlines immigration for qualified workers, entrepreneurs, and researchers. Standard employment visas (Salarié) remain available for positions not meeting Talent Passport criteria.
      </p>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        The French healthcare system consistently ranks among the world's best, and as a legal worker you'll have full access through the Sécurité Sociale. Your employer handles enrollment automatically through URSSAF contributions. The system covers approximately 70% of healthcare costs, with most workers adding a mutuelle (complementary insurance) for the remaining 30%.
      </p>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        France's 35-hour workweek, generous vacation time (5 weeks minimum), and strong worker protections create an attractive work-life balance. However, income tax rates are higher than many countries, typically 30-45% for professional salaries. The quality of life and social benefits often compensate for the tax burden.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Quick Decision Guide -->
    <section id="quick-decision" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Is a France Work Visa Right for You?</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Good Fit If You...</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Have a job offer from a French company</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Work in tech, finance, research, or skilled trades</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Value work-life balance and social protections</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Speak or are willing to learn French</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Want access to world-class public healthcare</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives If...</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You want to maximize take-home pay (high taxes)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You don't speak French and won't learn</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You need fast processing (2-4 months typical)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You prefer flexible work arrangements (strict labor laws)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You want to start your own business (separate visa)</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Official Requirements -->
    <section id="official-requirements" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Official Requirements</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Visa Categories</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Visa Type", "Duration", "Salary Requirement", "Best For"]}
        rows={[
          ["Talent Passport - Salarié Qualifié", "Up to 4 years", "2x minimum wage (~€3,600/month)", "Skilled employees with degree"],
          ["Talent Passport - Carte Bleue (EU Blue Card)", "Up to 4 years", "1.5x average salary (~€4,500/month)", "Highly qualified professionals"],
          ["Salarié (Standard Work Visa)", "1 year renewable", "At least minimum wage (SMIC)", "Jobs not meeting Talent criteria"],
          ["Talent Passport - Chercheur", "Up to 4 years", "Hosting agreement", "Researchers, scientists"],
          ["Talent Passport - Entrepreneur", "Up to 4 years", "€30,000 investment", "Business founders"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Eligibility Criteria</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Requirement", "Talent Passport", "Standard Salarié"]}
        rows={[
          ["Job Offer", "Required", "Required"],
          ["Employer Sponsorship", "Employer declaration only", "DREETS labor authorization"],
          ["Minimum Salary", "2x SMIC (~€3,600/month)", "At least SMIC"],
          ["Education", "Bachelor's degree minimum", "Depends on role"],
          ["Labor Market Test", "No", "Yes (employer proves no EU candidates)"],
          ["French Language", "Not required but helpful", "Not required but helpful"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Required Documents</h3>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Valid passport</strong> – At least 1 year validity recommended</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Long-stay visa application</strong> – France-Visas online portal</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Employment contract</strong> – French-language, signed by both parties</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Degree certificates</strong> – Translated and apostilled</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Proof of accommodation</strong> – Rental contract or employer housing</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Passport photos</strong> – ICAO compliant</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Health insurance</strong> – For initial period before Sécu enrollment</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Insurance Requirements -->
    <section id="insurance-requirements" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Insurance Requirements</h2>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
        <p class="text-green-800 font-medium">✓ Sécurité Sociale Enrollment is Automatic</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 text-sm mt-1">Once employed, your employer enrolls you in the French social security system. Coverage begins from your first day of work. Contributions are deducted automatically from salary (approximately 22% employee + 45% employer).</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">How French Healthcare Coverage Works</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Coverage Element", "Sécurité Sociale", "With Mutuelle Added"]}
        rows={[
          ["GP Consultation (€26.50)", "70% covered (€18.55)", "100% covered"],
          ["Specialist Visit", "70% covered", "100% covered"],
          ["Hospital Stay", "80% covered", "100% covered"],
          ["Prescriptions", "15-100% (drug dependent)", "100% covered"],
          ["Dental", "70% of tariff (often low)", "Up to 100% real costs"],
          ["Optical", "Minimal (~€4 for frames)", "€100-400 allowance"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Mutuelle (Complementary Insurance)</h3>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Since January 2016, all French employers must provide a mutuelle for employees, covering at least 50% of the premium. This complementary insurance covers the remaining 30% not reimbursed by Sécurité Sociale, plus better dental and optical coverage. You're automatically enrolled in your employer's group plan unless you opt out with proof of existing coverage.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
        <p class="text-amber-800 font-medium">Gap Coverage Needed: First Few Weeks</p>
        <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm mt-1">There's typically a 2-4 week gap between arrival and Carte Vitale issuance. You can still access healthcare (pay upfront, claim back later), but travel insurance or international coverage provides peace of mind for this transition period.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">What Sécurité Sociale Covers</h3>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Covered</h4>
          <ul class="text-neutral-600 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• GP and specialist consultations</li>
            <li>• Hospital care (public and private)</li>
            <li>• Prescription medications</li>
            <li>• Laboratory tests and imaging</li>
            <li>• Maternity care (100% covered)</li>
            <li>• Mental health (partial)</li>
            <li>• Emergency care</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Limited or Excluded</h4>
          <ul class="text-neutral-600 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• Dental (major work poorly covered)</li>
            <li>• Optical (very limited)</li>
            <li>• Alternative medicine</li>
            <li>• Cosmetic procedures</li>
            <li>• Care outside France</li>
            <li>• Private hospital room upgrades</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Recommended Providers -->
    <section id="recommended-providers" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
        For the transition period before Sécurité Sociale enrollment, or for additional global coverage, these international providers work well in France.
      </p>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Provider", "Best For", "France Network", "Monthly Cost", "Key Features"]}
        rows={[
          ["Allianz Care", "Expats wanting CFE alternative", "Extensive", "€150-350", "EU-regulated, global coverage"],
          ["AXA Global", "French company (local expertise)", "Excellent", "€180-400", "Strong France network, EU compliant"],
          ["Cigna Global", "Executives needing global mobility", "Very good", "€200-450", "Worldwide coverage included"],
          ["BUPA Global", "Mental health priority", "Good", "€200-400", "No therapy session limits"],
          ["CFE + Mutuelle", "Long-term France residents", "Full access", "€150-300", "Mirrors Sécu for expats"]
        ]}
      />

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
        <p class="text-blue-800 font-medium">CFE (Caisse des Français de l'Étranger)</p>
        <p class="text-blue-700 text-sm mt-1">French nationals abroad can join CFE, but so can some non-French long-term residents. CFE mimics Sécurité Sociale coverage and is popular with those who split time between France and other countries. Often paired with a mutuelle for complete coverage.</p>
      </div>

      <CTABox
        title="Compare International Health Plans for France"
        description="Get quotes from providers with strong French networks. Ensure coverage during your transition to Sécurité Sociale."
        buttonText="Compare Plans"
        buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
      />
    </section>

    <!-- Costs Breakdown -->
    <section id="costs" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Costs Breakdown</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Visa & Setup Costs</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Item", "Cost (EUR)", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Long-stay visa fee", "€99", "Paid at consulate"],
          ["OFII tax (arrival)", "€225", "Talent Passport; €200 for Salarié"],
          ["Carte de séjour renewal", "€225", "After initial visa"],
          ["Document translation", "€50-150", "Certified translations"],
          ["Degree apostille", "€0-50", "Country dependent"],
          ["Medical exam (if required)", "€60-100", "OFII medical"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Healthcare Costs</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Item", "Monthly Cost", "Who Pays", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Sécurité Sociale", "~22% of salary", "Split employer/employee", "Automatic deduction"],
          ["Employer Mutuelle", "€30-80", "50%+ employer paid", "Mandatory since 2016"],
          ["International bridge coverage", "€100-200", "Employee", "First 1-2 months only"],
          ["CFE (optional)", "€150-300", "Employee", "For global coverage"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Living Costs (Monthly)</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Category", "Paris", "Lyon/Other Cities", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Rent (1BR)", "€1,200-2,000", "€600-1,000", "Location varies significantly"],
          ["Utilities", "€100-180", "€80-150", "EDF electricity, gas"],
          ["Transport", "€84", "€60-70", "Navigo pass (Paris), TCL (Lyon)"],
          ["Food", "€400-600", "€300-450", "Mix of home/restaurants"],
          ["Healthcare (OOP)", "€0-50", "€0-50", "Minimal with mutuelle"]
        ]}
      />

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
        <p class="text-amber-800 font-medium">Tax Considerations</p>
        <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm mt-1">French income tax is progressive (11-45%) plus social charges (~22% employee share). A €60,000 gross salary yields approximately €3,500-3,800/month net after all deductions. Use an online French salary calculator to estimate your specific situation.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Application Timeline -->
    <section id="application-timeline" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Timeline</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Month 1-2</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Job Offer & Contract</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Secure job offer from French employer. Sign employment contract (contrat de travail). Employer prepares declaration or applies for work authorization (Salarié visa only).</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Month 2-3</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Visa Application</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Apply via France-Visas portal. Book appointment at French consulate. Submit documents, biometrics, and pay €99 fee. Processing takes 2-4 weeks typically.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Month 3-4</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Visa Issuance & Arrival</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Receive visa sticker in passport. Travel to France within validity period. Long-stay visa (VLS-TS) acts as residence permit for first year.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 1-2</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">OFII Validation</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Complete online OFII validation within 3 months of arrival. Pay €225 tax. Schedule medical if required. Receive validated visa allowing full rights.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 2-6</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Social Security & Carte Vitale</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Employer registers you with URSSAF. Apply for numéro de sécurité sociale (NIR). Carte Vitale (health card) arrives in 4-8 weeks. Can use paper attestation meanwhile.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Month 10-12</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Carte de Séjour Renewal</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Apply 2-4 months before visa expires at préfecture. Talent Passport can renew for 4 years. Salarié renews annually until qualifying for longer permits.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Real-World Scenarios -->
    <section id="scenarios" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Tech Worker to Paris</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Maria, 29, software engineer from Brazil. €55,000 salary qualifies for Talent Passport. Visa approved in 3 weeks. Employer provides group mutuelle. Carte Vitale received 5 weeks after start. Loves 35-hour week and 5 weeks vacation.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Smooth process, excellent healthcare coverage, great work-life balance</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Researcher in Lyon</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Dr. Ahmed, 35, postdoc from Egypt. Hosting agreement from CNRS qualifies for Chercheur Talent Passport. Process took 2 months including degree verification. Full Sécu coverage from day one.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Straightforward for researchers, university handled paperwork</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Chef Without Degree</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">James, 32, British chef. No degree means standard Salarié visa required. Employer had to prove no EU candidates available (labor market test). Process took 4 months. Eventually approved for Michelin restaurant position.</p>
          <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Longer process without degree, but possible for skilled roles</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">American with Pre-existing Condition</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Sarah, 40, has Type 1 diabetes. Moves to Paris for finance role. Nervous about coverage gap. Sécurité Sociale covers insulin fully once enrolled. Kept international plan for first 6 weeks during transition. No issues with pre-existing condition.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: French system covers pre-existing conditions—no exclusions</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Family Relocation to Toulouse</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Chen family moves for Airbus position. Husband's Talent Passport covers family. Wife and 2 children get ayant droit status for Sécurité Sociale. School enrollment straightforward. International mutuelle tops up dental for braces.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Family covered under one visa, children in excellent public schools</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Salary Below Talent Threshold</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Elena, 26, marketing coordinator. €32,000 salary below Talent Passport threshold. Required standard Salarié visa with labor market test. Employer struggled to justify not hiring EU candidate. Visa eventually denied.</p>
          <p class="text-red-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Below threshold + common profession = rejection risk</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Common Mistakes -->
    <section id="common-mistakes" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">1. Not Validating OFII Within 3 Months</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">You must complete OFII online validation within 3 months of arrival. Missing this deadline can void your visa and create serious legal issues. Set a reminder immediately upon arrival.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">2. Arriving Without Bridge Insurance</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Carte Vitale takes 4-8 weeks to arrive. While you can technically access care (pay and claim back), having travel or international insurance for the first 1-2 months provides peace of mind and easier claims.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">3. Underestimating French Bureaucracy</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Every process takes longer than expected. Préfecture appointments book up months ahead. RIB (bank account) needed for everything. Build in buffer time and expect multiple visits for any administrative task.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">4. Assuming English is Sufficient</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">While Paris tech companies often use English, all official documents, medical appointments, and daily life require French. Healthcare providers outside major cities rarely speak English. Learning basic French is essential.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">5. Not Starting Renewal Early Enough</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Préfecture appointments for visa renewal can book 3-4 months out. Start the renewal process 4-5 months before expiry. A récépissé (receipt) allows you to stay legally while waiting, but late applications cause stress.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Healthcare Access -->
    <section id="healthcare-access" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Healthcare System Access</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        France's healthcare system is world-renowned, ranking consistently in the top 5 globally. The system combines public hospitals, private clinics, and a network of independent practitioners. As a legal worker, you have the same access as French citizens.
      </p>

